! --- Version 6.42, Level 110325 to Version TNG-7.0.0, Level 140913
!     1) Add new input groups in the control file for FLARES and ROADS,
!        so the control file dataset is changed to TNG-3.0
!     2) Treat FLARE sources as a discrete source type throughout code
!        rather than as a subset of POINTS (introduced in v6.42_x1.0)
!        NOTES: 1. This implementation allows for flare source data to
!                  be provided in one or more FLEMARB.DAT files.
!                  It does not allow for inputs to the control file.
!               2. Although the FLEMARB.DAT file format allows a
!                  non-vertical exit velocity, this is not fully
!                  implemented and so is not currently supported.
!               3. The FLEMARB.DAT file format allows either the
!                  buoyancy and momentum fluxes or the exit temperature
!                  and velocities to be used, but the fluxes are not
!                  currently supported.
!               4. The flare source is similar to the point source
!                  except that its location is updated each timestep as
!                  the flame tip moves with the wind direction.  This
!                  precludes building downwash.
!        REMOVED:  RDFL_CF, RDTIFL2, SWAPTIEM2, SKIPHDFL2, RDFL2,
!        NEW:      FL1.PUF
